{
  "texts": [
    "The difference in Bard's performance across the two studies may reflect the variations in question format, complexity, or training data relevance, which may favor certain contexts over others.",
    "Chen et al.",
    "evaluated ChatGPT-3.5 and Bing AI GPT-4.0 on 5 years of OITE questions [53].",
    "ChatGPT-3.5 averaged 55%, while Bing AI GPT-4.0 scored 80%, outperforming both ChatGPT and orthopedic residents (62.1).",
    "Future research should focus on improving generative AI models like GPT-4 in orthopedic education by expanding their knowledge base, integrating real-time updates from medical literature and clinical practice, refining their ability to handle complex clinical reasoning and image interpretation, and enhancing their accuracy and reliability in image-based questions."
  ]
}